results.name: Expansion of (eta(q) * eta(q^6))^7 / (eta(q^2) * eta(q^3))^5 in powers of q.
comment: Ramanujan theta functions: f(q) (see A121373), phi(q) (A000122), psi(q) (A010054), chi(q) (A000700).
Cubic AGM theta functions: a(q) (see A004016), b(q) (A005928), c(q) (A005882).
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
Michael Somos, Introduction to Ramanujan theta functions
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Ramanujan Theta Functions
formula: Expansion of q * (phi(-q) * psi(q^3))^3 / (phi(-q^3) * psi(q)) in powers of q where phi(), psi() are Ramanujan theta functions.
Expansion of (b(q)^2 / b(q^2)) * (c(q^2)^2 / c(q)) / 3 in powers of q where b(), c() are cubic AGM theta functions.
G.f. is a period 1 Fourier series which satisfies f(-1 / (6 t)) = 6 (t / i)^2 f(t) where q = exp(2 Pi i t). - _Michael Somos_, Sep 19 2013
Convolution of A006353 and A226235. - _Michael Somos_, Sep 19 2013
mathematica: a[ n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ q (QPochhammer[ q] QPochhammer[ q^6])^7 / (QPochhammer[ q^2] QPochhammer[ q^3])^5, {q, 0, n}]; (* _Michael Somos_, Sep 19 2013 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = local(A); if( n<1, 0, n--; A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( (eta(x + A) * eta(x^6 + A))^7 / (eta(x^2 + A) * eta(x^3 + A))^5, n))};
(Sage) A = ModularForms( Gamma0(6), 2, prec=50) . basis(); A[1] - 7*A[2]; # _Michael Somos_, Sep 19 2013
